taly).\n\n==Results and fixtures==\n{{Main|Italy national football team results (2010\u201329)}}\n\n{{legend2|#CCFFCC|Win|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#FFFFCC|Draw|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#FFCCCC|Loss|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#BBBBBB|Void|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#FFFFFF|Fixtures|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n<!--\nCriteria for inclusion: All upcoming results (future) and any results within the last 12 months (past)\n-->\n\n===2019===\n{{football box collapsible|format=1\n|date = 8 June 2019\n|round = [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying Group J|UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying]]\n|time = 20:45 [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]] ([[UTC+02:00]])\n|team1 = {{fb-rt|GRE}}\n|score = 0\u20133\n|team2 = {{fb|ITA}}\n|report = https://www.uefa.com/european-qualifiers/season=2020/matches/round=2001086/match=2026090/index.html\n|goals1 = \n|goals2 = \n*[[Nicol\u00f2 Barella|Barella]] {{goal|23}}\n*[[Lorenzo Insigne|Insigne]] {{goal|30}}\n*[[Leonardo Bonucci|Bonucci]] {{goal|33}}\n|location = [[Athens]], Greece\n|stadium = [[Olympic Stadium (Athens)|Olympic Stadium]]\n|attendance = 19,828\n|referee = [[Anthony Taylor (referee)|Anthony Taylor]] ([[The Football Association|England]])\n|result = W\n}}\n{{football box collapsible|format=1\n|date = 11 June 2019\n|round = [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying Group J|UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying]]\n|time = 20:45 [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]] ([[UTC+02:00]])\n|team1 = {{fb-rt|ITA}}\n|score = 2\u20131\n|team2 = {{fb|BIH}}\n|report = https://www.uefa.com/european-qualifiers/season=2020/matches/round=2001086/match=2026164/index.html\n|goals1 = \n*[[Lorenzo Insigne|Insigne]] {{goal|49}}\n*[[Marco Verratti|Verratti]] {{goal|86}}\n|goals2 = \n*[[Edin D\u017eeko|D\u017eeko]] {{goal|32}}\n|location = [[Turin]], Italy\n|stadium = [[Juventus Stadium]]\n|attendance = 29,100\n|referee = [[Xavier Estrada Fern\u00e1ndez]] ([[Royal Spanish Football Federation|Spain]])\n|result = W\n}}\n{{football box collapsible|format=1